summary:
The Security Council:

1. Allows deliveries of items in the annex of resolution 2111 (2013) to Somali people;
2. Permits vessels carrying arms for defensive purposes to enter Somali ports temporarily without violating the arms embargo, provided the items remain on board;
3. Requests the Committee to publish an implementation assistance notice on arms embargo restrictions on Somalia and Eritrea within 90 days;
4. Reiterates that arms sold to the Federal Government of Somalia's (FGS) security forces may not be resold or transferred to others;
5. Welcomes FGS' efforts to improve weapons registration and calls for a baseline inventory of military equipment, arms, and ammunition;
6. Requests FGS to report to the Security Council by 15 April 2016 and 15 October 2016 on its security forces;
7. Recalls FGS' responsibility to notify the Committee on arms deliveries and calls for improved timeliness and content of notifications;
8. Urges Member States to coordinate with Somalia's National Security Adviser and follow notification procedures;
9. Urges cooperation between AMISOM and Somali National Army to document and register captured military equipment;
10. Calls for enhanced civilian oversight of FGS' security forces and investigation of human rights violations;
11. Underlines the importance of timely payment of salaries to Somali security forces;
12. Reaffirms the arms embargo on Eritrea;
13. Expresses concern at corruption and diversion of public resources in Somalia;
14. Welcomes FGS' efforts to improve financial management procedures;
15. Reaffirms Somalia's sovereignty over its natural resources;
16. Reiterates concern that the petroleum sector could drive conflict and calls for a resource-sharing arrangement;
17. Reaffirms the ban on the import and export of Somali charcoal and condemns ongoing exports;
18. Welcomes efforts of the Combined Maritime Forces to disrupt charcoal export and import.
